==English==
===Etymology===
First attested in [[w:1340|1340]], from [[Old French]] [[chaméléon]], from [[Latin]] [[chamaeleon]], from [[Greek]] [[khamaileon]], from [[chthon]] ''earth'' + [[leon]] ''lion''. See also [[chamomile]].
===Noun===
#A small to mid-size [[reptile]], and one of the best known [[lizard]] families able to change color and project its long tongue.
#A person with inconstant behavior.
#A constellation in the southern hemisphere near [[Apus]] and [[Mensa]].
